  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Descriptions:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage and prepare the measurements and cost estimates for the construction projects from initial calculations to the final accounts.</li><li>Prepare contract documents in accordance to the regulations.</li><li><li>Evaluate and prepare progress payments to subcontractors / suppliers / service providers.</li></li><li>Prepare cost analysis and monitor project overruns to ensure the objectives of the project is achieved.</li><li>Access payment and variation works to subcontractors to facilitate the smooth workflow process.</li><li>Communicate with the management, sub-contractors and keeps track of the progression of the sub-contract.</li><li>Any other adhoc tasks assigned by superior.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering, Quantity Surveying, or other related disciplines.</li><li>Minimum 2-5 years of experience in Quantity Surveying.</li><li>Proficient in PDF measurement or any other measurement software will be added advantages.</li><li>Familiar with various standard forms of contract (e.g., SIA, PSSCOC, FIDIC).</li><li>Location: East.</li></ul>",
